			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I think what the core issue here is that something unpredictable happened.<BR>
<BR>
For some reason, people want Norrath to be predictable. Always the same mobs in a zone, always at the same place. And suddenly when their expectations aren't met, it's somehow 'unfair'.<BR>
<BR>
Verant has said that there are no 'safe zones' in the game and I'm happy with that. There are some places that are 'safer' than others, but knowing that even Greater Faydark can have something which can kill even after all these levels gives the game a nice edge of excitement that I like.<BR>
<BR>
This is how a dangerous world should be. Nothing is certain. Nothing is fixed. There are no promises, there are no guarantees.<BR>
<BR>
Jory
				</font>
			</td>

