			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Bemused:<BR>
<BR>
Why should they?<BR>
<BR>
What difference does it make if a mob is being played by a GM or not?<BR>
<BR>
As it is, if a GM mob kills you through straight melee, you loose no XP. You only loose XP if a DoT spell or GM pet kills you or if you fall into lava or drown or the like.<BR>
<BR>
People get killed all the time by things they didn't expect and which are much harder than they are. Dragoon Zytl might spawn in WC and lay waste to everyone around the Toll Booth. No one complains to Verant when they loose XP that way.<BR>
<BR>
Death is death. Whether the monster is controlled by an AI or a GM player, why should that matter?<BR>
<BR>
Regards,<BR>
Jory
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
